Here is an example of converting a UE4 FString to a std::string in C++ :

```cpp
FString UE4String = "Hello World"; 

std::string StdString;

// Convert FString to std::string
StdString.assign(TCHAR_TO_UTF8(*UE4String)); 

// Or use the convenience function
StdString = UE4String.ToString();

// Use the std::string 
std::cout << StdString << std::endl;
```

The key points are:

- UE4 uses TCHAR strings (FString) instead of regular std::string.
- To convert to std::string, you need to use the TCHAR_TO_UTF8 macro on the FString.
- FString has a convenience ToString() method that handles the conversion.
- Once converted, you can use the std::string normally.

So in summary, to go from FString to std::string, you just need to use the TCHAR_TO_UTF8 macro or the ToString() method on the FString.

