You can use the `react-quill` npm module to add a rich text editor in your Next.js/TypeScript project. It is a React-based editor that provides a lot of features like formatting, styling, and embedding media. Here's how you can install it:

```
npm install react-quill
```

Then, you can import it in your component and use it like this:

```
import ReactQuill from 'react-quill';
import 'react-quill/dist/quill.snow.css';

function Editor() {
  const [content, setContent] = useState('');

  function handleChange(value) {
    setContent(value);
  }

  return (
    <ReactQuill value={content} onChange={handleChange} />
  );
}

export default Editor;
```

In this example, we are using `useState` to store the editor's content and `onChange` to update it. The `react-quill` package also requires you to import its CSS file to apply styles to the editor.

To add a dark mode to Chatall, you can follow these steps:

1. Add a "Dark Mode" toggle button:

```html
<button id="darkModeToggle">Toggle Dark Mode</button>
```

2. Add a class "dark-mode" to the body:

```html
<body>
  <!-- other elements --> 
</body>
```

3. Add a click handler to the toggle button to add/remove the "dark-mode" class:

```js
const darkModeToggle = document.getElementById("darkModeToggle");
darkModeToggle.addEventListener("click", () => {
  document.body.classList.toggle("dark-mode");
});
```

4. Add CSS rules for "dark-mode":

```css
body.dark-mode {
  background: #1a1a1a;
  color: #fff;
}

body.dark-mode a {
  color: #09f;
}

/* Other selectors... */ 
``` 

5. Adjust the colors of all elements for the dark mode using CSS. For example:

```css
.dark-mode .chat-message {
  background: #333;
  border-color: #555;
}

.dark-mode .chat-input {
  background: #333;
  border-color: #555;
  color: #fff;
}
```

6. Make sure to add the "dark-mode" class to additional elements as needed for full dark mode styling.

